\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces NL\% predicts express-link saving across 28 cells. RL-WS (red diamonds) raises the saving curve above both greedy (blue circles) and FBfly (green squares). On high-NL ($\ge $77\%) cells, RL-WS strictly dominates FBfly; on low-NL cells, the gap shrinks to single-cycle scale and the deployment-classifier signal is to fall back to FBfly. Pooled Spearman $\rho (\mathrm  {NL\%}, \text  {RL-WS saving})=0.83$ ($p=6.8\times 10^{-8}$).}}{7}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ml_nonlocality}{{4}{7}{NL\% predicts express-link saving across 28 cells. RL-WS (red diamonds) raises the saving curve above both greedy (blue circles) and FBfly (green squares). On high-NL ($\ge $77\%) cells, RL-WS strictly dominates FBfly; on low-NL cells, the gap shrinks to single-cycle scale and the deployment-classifier signal is to fall back to FBfly. Pooled Spearman $\rho (\mathrm {NL\%}, \text {RL-WS saving})=0.83$ ($p=6.8\times 10^{-8}$)}{figure.4}{}}
